Osborne Says U.K. Businesses Seeing ‘Massive’ Cut in Tax Rate

-- B y   G o n z a l o   V i n a
-- 
2011-10-03T07:25:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-03/osborne-says-u-k-businesses-seeing-massive-cut-in-tax-rate.html
Chancellor of the Exchequer  George
Osborne  said Britain’s companies are already benefiting from a
cut in corporation tax and that he would not do more because
the Treasury can’t afford it.  “Lower taxes are only permanent when you get the public
finances in order,” Osborne told BBC Radio 4 today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gonzalo Vina in London at 
